classes directly since it involves parsing with Jackson. Given the requirement to modify a \\\"provided file,\\\" I think a migration approach might be better due to its value. Testing coverage for dynamic-access call sites looks important too. I should consider how to include the right classes for proper metadata generation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing migration options**\\n\\nI see there's no built-in migration available, which complicates things. I might consider using `akka.serialization.jackson.JacksonMigration`, but that’s an abstract class with no compile or run features. This raises a potential issue about maintaining a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and the generated test class files. We’ve added a helper migration in the same file, but there are no new dynamic-access report classes created. The target class for dynamic access is MigratedOrderMigration, but it serves merely as a test helper.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying dynamic reporting rules**\\n\\nI’m figuring out that the rule pertains to dynamic-access report classes, specifically regarding library classes. I should also consider handling unsupported dynamic class loading, though it isn't open-ended. I think I might need to adjust the import order, reorganizing to check Java first but keeping it minimal isn't strictly necessary. Ultimately, I want a concise final response that identifies current coverage and notes that I added a migration test, while mentioning that no tests ran due to the instruction.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a new Scala test in:\n\n`tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-serialization-jackson_2.13/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_serialization_jackson_2_13/Akka_serialization_jackson_2_13Test.scala`\n\nCurrent coverage identified:\n- CBOR serializer round-trips Akka Jackson module types: `ActorRef`, `Address`, `FiniteDuration`.\n- Existing separate test covers JSON serializer with `t